body:
Description
I have create a SKBitmap and SKCanvas and then i call dispose for both SKBitmap and SKCanvas but the memory is not released. I have the checked the memory usage using Visual Studio. I have compare the third and first snapshot after the dispose method but it holds some bytes. Attached screenshots shows that memory is not released after disposing the object.

Code

        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Starting");
            Console.ReadLine(); // Starting snapshot
            MemoryCheck();
            Console.WriteLine("disposed");
            Console.ReadLine(); // Final snapshot
        }
        static void MemoryCheck()
        {
            SKBitmap bitmap = new SKBitmap(10, 10);
            SKCanvas sKCanvas = new SKCanvas(bitmap);
            bitmap.Dispose();
            sKCanvas.Dispose();
            bitmap = null;
            sKCanvas = null;
        }

Expected Behavior
Second snapshot Memory Should be downed to first snapshot. 

Actual Behavior
Second snapshot holding extra memory which is not released even after calling dispose.

I have ensured this with 1.59.3 And latest version, still issue is not resolved in latest version,
this issue is created with the follow up with the following issue - https://github.com/mono/SkiaSharp/issues/1009

Basic Information

Version with issue: 1.59.3 And 2.80.2
IDE: Visual Studio 2017
Platform Target Frameworks: .NET Core 2.0

Skia sharp version - 1.59.3
<img width="960" alt="Skia Sharp - 1 59 3" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/34718301/97434740-787fa080-1945-11eb-89c1-f08919aeba58.PNG">

Skia sharp version - 2.80.2
<img width="957" alt="SkiaSharp - 2 80 2" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/34718301/97434744-7a496400-1945-11eb-962a-30d20e4c116d.PNG">

Here is the project to reproduce the issue:

[Memory checking.zip](https://github.com/mono/SkiaSharp/files/5451756/Memory.checking.zip)
